  "texts": [
    "The linearized equations of motion take on a particularly simple form, as we now show.",
    "First, using Eq.",
    "(30) we find that to second order in z, z the TDVP Hamiltonian can be written asH(z, z) = E 0 + 1 2 (z z) A B B * A * z z + O(z 3),(81)where E 0 = ⟨ψ 0 |H|ψ 0 ⟩, and we have defined the matrices A and B asA im,jn = (E m -E i)δ ij δ mn + V mj,in -V mj,ni,(82)B im,jn = V mn,ij -V mn,ji.",
    "(83)Note that A is Hermitian, and B is symmetric.",
    "( 81), we find that the linearized equations of motion areż ż = -i A B -B * -A * z z."
